text:
the venu can look way better than it is, they have a kitchen in the dining area and two sheets of blankets covering the kitchen part. barely any space but dueable. custmer service was good but could be better by checking up on us or simple refills on our drinks. we got the garlic chicken for an appetitizer and spicy meso ramen for our entre. 

     for starters the garlic chicken was very fatty and crispy, which is how it should be. they had a dressing that gets drizzled on top of the chicken and it really compliments the crispy chicken! ( the dressing is my fave part of this dish ) 


        lastly the spicy ramen, the noddles were to die for perfectly cooked off tops! the soup broth is thick and you can taste the yolks inside the broth. there was slices of beef in the soup that were a weebit raw but perfectly cooked. the meat made the soup better. overall the place was pretty yummy.
